dcterms:description: Superclassing ImageNet dataset is a hierarchical subset of ImageNet that contains broad superclasses, each subsuming several of the original ImageNet classes. It consists of 10 superclasses with a total of 253 subclasses, designed to help identify patterns of misclassification in deep neural networks.
dcterms:title: Superclassing ImageNet dataset

dcterms:description: ImageNet is a large-scale hierarchical image database that contains a vast number of images organized into categories. It serves as a benchmark for image classification tasks and is widely used for training deep learning models.
dcterms:title: ImageNet
